perl-text-unidecode|-----handy-ruler------------------------------------------------------|
perl-text-unidecode: perl-text-unidecode (US-ASCII transliterations of Unicode text)
perl-text-unidecode:
perl-text-unidecode: Text::Unidecode provides a function, `unidecode(...)' that takes
perl-text-unidecode: Unicode data and tries to represent it in US-ASCII characters
perl-text-unidecode: (i.e., the universally displayable characters between 0x00 and 0x7F).
perl-text-unidecode: The representation is almost always an attempt at *transliteration*
perl-text-unidecode: -- i.e., conveying, in Roman letters, the pronunciation expressed by
perl-text-unidecode: the text in some other writing system. 
perl-text-unidecode:
perl-text-unidecode: http://search.cpan.org/dist/Text-Unidecode/
perl-text-unidecode: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
